Only necessary if the value differs from More Sparkles!.

description.value: Innate: After casting an ability, Zoe's next basic attack or Spell Thief bubble within 5 seconds becomes a non-projectile and deals 16 − 130 (based on level) (+ 20% AP) bonus magic damage.

disp_name.description:
Name of the ability
Only necessary if the value differs from Paddle Star.

blurb.value: Zoe fires a missile that she can redirect in flight, which deals more damage the longer it flies in a straight line.

description.value: Active: Zoe shoots a star in the target direction that collides with the first enemy hit, dealing magic damage in a small area, reduced to 80% to enemies hit beyond the first. The total damage is increased by 0% − 150% (based on distance traveled).

leveling.value: Minimum Magic Damage:»7 − 50 (based on level) (+ 50 / 80 / 110 / 140 / 170) (+ 60% AP)«Maximum Magic Damage:17.5 − 125 (based on level) (+ 125 / 200 / 275 / 350 / 425) (+ 150% AP)

description2.value: If the star does not hit an enemy, it lingers at maximum range for 1 second, allowing Paddle Star to be recast after 0.25 seconds in the duration.

description3.value: Recast: Zoe redirects the star to a new location near her, resetting its damage modifier on cast. The redirected star can travel beyond the new target location, continuing forward until it moves more than 800 units from Zoe.

description4.value: Paddle Star's recast can be used while affected by crowd control.

disp_name.description:
Name of the ability
Only necessary if the value differs from Spell Thief.

blurb.value: Zoe can pick up the remnants of enemy summoner spell and active item casts and cast them once herself. Whenever she casts a summoner spell, she gains 3 missiles that fire at the nearest target.

description.value: Passive - Spell Thief: Whenever enemy champions cast a summoner spell or item active, they drop the corresponding Spell Shard onto the ground that grants sight over a 100-radius area and remains for 40 seconds. Some enemy minions spawn with random Spell Shards that only drop to the ground for 20 seconds if killed by Zoe.

description2.value: Collecting a Spell Shard allows Zoe to activate Spell Thief within the next 60 seconds. She can replace her current Spell Thief active by moving directly onto another Spell Shard.

description3.value: Active: Zoe mimics the active of the collected Spell Shard.

description4.value: Passive - Wheeeee: Casting Spell Thief or one of her own summoner spells grants Zoe  bonus movement speed for the next few seconds, and summons three bubbles that orbit her for the next 10 seconds.

leveling4.value: Bonus Movement Speed:30 / 40 / 50 / 60 / 70%Bonus Movement Speed Duration:2 / 2.25 / 2.5 / 2.75 / 3

description5.value: If Zoe is not immobilized she hurls one bubble at a time at the nearest enemy in range, prioritizing her attack target, dealing magic damage.

leveling5.value: Magic Damage Per Orb:»25 / 35 / 45 / 55 / 65 (+ 13.3% AP)«Total Magic Damage:75 / 105 / 135 / 165 / 195 (+ 40% AP)

notes.value: * Mimics the details of the mimicked active. Minions that can drop Spell Shards are marked with a tied cosmic balloon that floats above them. Minions do not drop a shard for Hextech Gunblade or Teleport. Zoe utilizes an attack-like animation whenever one of the bubbles hurls itself at an enemy, making it look as if she can attack while moving. Zoe cannot steal consumables, trinkets, component items, or items that create deployable or persistent effects. Some actives are excluded for balance purposes. disp_name.description:
Name of the ability
Only necessary if the value differs from Sleepy Trouble Bubble.

blurb.value: Causes the target to become drowsy, then fall asleep. The first source of damage that breaks the sleep is doubled, up to a cap.

description.value: Active: Zoe kicks a bubble in the target direction that bursts on the first enemy hit, or else forming a trap at maximum range for 5 seconds that arms after 0.8 seconds. The bubble can only move through terrain once but may do so indefinitely, can only move up to 650 units once outside terrain, and will fall short if it would enter terrain again.

description2.value: The bubble deals magic damage on contact with an enemy and renders them drowsy for 1.4 seconds, which gradually slows them, after which they fall asleep for 2.25 seconds. Zoe will gain obscured vision of the target while they're asleep if they are not visible.

description3.value: The next non- persistent non- minion damage taken by the sleeping target consumes the debuff to deal  bonus true damage equal to the post-mitigation damage dealt, capped at Sleepy Trouble Bubble's damage. The bonus damage is dealt before the triggering damage.

disp_name.description:
Name of the ability
Only necessary if the value differs from Portal Jump.

blurb.value: Blink to a nearby position for 1 second. Then blink back.

description.value: Active: Zoe dives into a portal that she opens beneath her, blinking to the target location for 0.75 seconds, during which she sets her movement speed to a static 0 and has unobstructed vision. After 1 second, she blinks back to her cast location.

description2.value: Zoe is unable to basic attack and cast her abilities and movement spells for 0.75 seconds after casting Portal Jump and for 0.5 seconds after blinking back.
